{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1775841339513,"sessionID":"ses_2879c0ebbffeE6Frd5ny1RkJ5L","part":{"id":"prt_d78641af8001MKmnA6cg5QtYK9","messageID":"msg_d786409f2001L82y7nwz76DzIK","sessionID":"ses_2879c0ebbffeE6Frd5ny1RkJ5L","type":"tool","tool":"write","callID":"toolu_27089e2343c1450694551689","state":{"status":"error","input":{"content":"# Proposal: WorkloadManager HTTP Service Framework\n\n## AR Information\n- **AR ID**: AR-004\n- **Title**: WorkloadManager HTTP ÊúçÂä°Ê°ÜÊû∂\n- **Module**: pkg/workloadmanager\n- **Language**: Go\n- **Size**: M\n\n## 1. Purpose\n\n### Background\nThe WorkloadManager module needs to expose its functionality via HTTP APIs for external clients and internal services to interact with AgentRuntime and CodeInterpreter resources in the Kubernetes cluster.\n\n### Goal\nProvide a production-ready HTTP service framework in `pkg/workloadmanager` that:\n- Serves RESTful APIs for AgentRuntime and CodeInterpreter CRUD operations\n- Integrates with the `github.com/volcano-sh/agentcube/client-go` library for Kubernetes API access\n- Follows Kubernetes controller patterns and best practices\n\n### Value\n- Enables external systems to manage AgentRuntime and CodeInterpreter resources programmatically\n- Provides a standardized HTTP interface layer on top of the Kubernetes client\n- Supports observability, middleware extensibility, and graceful shutdown\n\n---\n\n## 2. Scope\n\n### In-Scope\n1. **HTTP Server Implementation**\n   - HTTP server with configurable host/port\n   - Graceful shutdown handling\n   - Health check endpoints (`/healthz`, `/readyz`)\n\n2. **REST API Endpoints**\n   - AgentRuntime CRUD: `GET/POST/PUT/DELETE /api/v1/namespaces/{namespace}/agentruntimes`\n   - AgentRuntime status: `GET/PATCH /api/v1/namespaces/{namespace}/agentruntimes/{name}/status`\n   - CodeInterpreter CRUD: `GET/POST/PUT/DELETE /api/v1/namespaces/{namespace}/codeinterpreters`\n   - CodeInterpreter status: `GET/PATCH /api/v1/namespaces/{namespace}/codeinterpreters/{name}/status`\n   - List/watch operations for both resources\n\n3. **Client Integration**\n   - Use `client-go` library to interact with Kubernetes API\n   - Proper config loading (in-cluster, kubeconfig)\n   - Client reuse and lifecycle management\n\n4. **Middleware & Utilities**\n   - Request logging and metrics\n   - Error handling and response formatting\n   - Authentication/authorization hooks (pluggable)\n\n### Out-of-Scope\n- Custom Resource Definitions (CRDs) ‚Äî already defined in `pkg/apis/runtime/v1alpha1`\n- Controller/reconciler logic ‚Äî separate concern\n- WebSocket or streaming APIs\n- Rate limiting (future enhancement)\n\n---\n\n## 3. Impact Analysis\n\n### Dependencies\n| Dependency | Version | Purpose |\n|------------|---------|---------|\n| github.com/volcano-sh/agentcube/client-go | local | Kubernetes typed client |\n| k8s.io/client-go/rest | latest | Low-level REST client |\n| k8s.io/apimachinery/pkg/runtime | latest | Object serialization |\n| k8s.io/apimachinery/pkg/api/errors | latest | Kubernetes API errors |\n\n### Code Structure\n```\npkg/workloadmanager/\n‚îú‚îÄ‚îÄ server.go           # HTTP server implementation\n‚îú‚îÄ‚îÄ router.go           # Route definitions\n‚îú‚îÄ‚îÄ handler/\n‚îÇ   ‚îú‚îÄ‚îÄ agentruntime.go # AgentRuntime handlers\n‚îÇ   ‚îî‚îÄ‚îÄ codeinterpreter.go # CodeInterpreter handlers\n‚îú‚îÄ‚îÄ middleware/\n‚îÇ   ‚îú‚îÄ‚îÄ logging.go\n‚îÇ   ‚îú‚îÄ‚îÄ metrics.go\n‚îÇ   ‚îî‚îÄ‚îÄ auth.go\n‚îî‚îÄ‚îÄ client/\n    ‚îî‚îÄ‚îÄ client.go       # Kubernetes client wrapper\n```\n\n### Testing Strategy\n- Unit tests for handlers and middleware\n- Integration tests with fake clientset\n- End-to-end tests against mock Kubernetes API server\n\n### Risks\n- **Client resource management**: Must ensure proper client reuse to avoid resource leaks\n- **API compatibility**: Future changes to client-go may require updates\n- **Error propagation**: Kubernetes API errors must be properly translated to HTTP status codes\n\n---\n\n## 4. Alternatives Considered\n\n### Option 1: Standard Go net/http (Selected)\n- **Pros**: Full control, no extra dependencies, lightweight\n- **Cons**: Must implement routing, middleware from scratch\n- **Decision**: Selected for maximum flexibility and minimal dependencies\n\n### Option 2: Gin/Echo Framework\n- **Pros**: Rich routing, middleware ecosystem, validation\n- **Cons**: Additional dependency, potential version drift\n- **Decision**: Rejected ‚Äî adds unnecessary complexity for Kubernetes controller context\n\n### Option 3: Kubernetes API Server Aggregation\n- **Pros**: Native Kubernetes integration, authentication\n- **Cons**: Complex setup, requires API server configuration\n- **Decision**: Rejected ‚Äî separate feature, not within current scope\n\n### Option 4: gRPC + grpc-gateway\n- **Pros**: Type-safe, streaming support\n- **Cons**: Requires proto definitions, additional complexity\n- **Decision**: Rejected ‚Äî gRPC not required for current use case\n\n---\n\n## 5. Implementation Plan\n\n### Phase 1: Core Server\n- [ ] Implement `server.go` with graceful shutdown\n- [ ] Add health check endpoints\n\n### Phase 2: Client Integration\n- [ ] Create Kubernetes client wrapper\n- [ ] Integrate with client-go `Clientset`\n\n### Phase 3: API Handlers\n- [ ] Implement AgentRuntime CRUD handlers\n- [ ] Implement CodeInterpreter CRUD handlers\n- [ ] Add list/watch support\n\n### Phase 4: Middleware\n- [ ] Request logging\n- [ ] Metrics collection\n- [ ] Error handling\n\n### Phase 5: Testing\n- [ ] Unit tests\n- [ ] Integration with fake clientset\n\n---\n\n## 6. Acceptance Criteria\n\n1. HTTP server starts and listens on configured port\n2. Health endpoints return 200 OK\n3. All CRUD operations for AgentRuntime work correctly\n4. All CRUD operations for CodeInterpreter work correctly\n5. Kubernetes client is properly managed (no leaks)\n6. Middleware logging captures request details\n7. Errors are properly mapped to HTTP status codes\n8. Unit tests pass with >80% coverage for handlers","filePath":"/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-MiniMax-M2.5_20260410T163134Z/proposal.md"},"error":"You must read file /home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-MiniMax-M2.5_20260410T163134Z/proposal.md before overwriting it. Use the Read tool first","time":{"start":1775841339505,"end":1775841339510}}}}
