{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1775841344191,"sessionID":"ses_2879c0ebbffeE6Frd5ny1RkJ5L","part":{"id":"prt_d786475db001BlKqL8h5KXDCJE","messageID":"msg_d786468ab001S3OCEEqjD2FxZa","sessionID":"ses_2879c0ebbffeE6Frd5ny1RkJ5L","type":"tool","tool":"read","callID":"toolu_af501d47d3d34c24afa98bfe","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"filePath":"/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-MiniMax-M2.5_20260410T163134Z/proposal.md"},"output":"<path>/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-MiniMax-M2.5_20260410T163134Z/proposal.md</path>\n<type>file</type>\n<content>\n1: # Proposal: AR-003 ‚Äî CRD ÂÖ±‰∫´Á±ªÂûã‰∏éÂ∏∏Èáè\n2: \n3: ## Summary\n4: \n5: Define shared types, constants, and utility functions in the `pkg/apis/runtime/v1alpha1` module to support the AgentRuntime and CodeInterpreter CRDs. This includes API group constants, resource identifiers, and common types used across multiple CRDs.\n6: \n7: ## Purpose\n8: \n9: The shared types and constants provide:\n10: \n11: - **API group identification**: Consistent GroupName and Version constants for scheme registration\n12: - **Resource naming**: Standardized plural resource names for Kubernetes API routing\n13: - **Client-go compatibility**: Types consumed by generated client library\n14: - **Type safety**: Shared constants prevent hardcoded strings across the codebase\n15: \n16: These shared definitions are consumed by:\n17: - pkg/apis (type definitions)\n18: - client-go library (generated client code)\n19: - Controllers (workload manager reads CRs)\n20: - Helm CRDs (generated from types)\n21: \n22: ## Scope\n23: \n24: ### Deliverables\n25: \n26: | Deliverable | Path | Description |\n27: |-------------|------|-------------|\n28: | Constants | `pkg/apis/runtime/v1alpha1/register.go` | GroupName, Version, SchemeGroupVersion |\n29: | Resource helpers | `pkg/apis/runtime/v1alpha1/register.go` | Resource(), AddKnownTypes |\n30: | Shared types | `pkg/apis/runtime/v1alpha1/types.go` | TargetPort, ContainerTemplateSpec, AuthMode, etc. |\n31: \n32: ### Constants\n33: \n34: ```go\n35: const (\n36:     GroupName = \"runtime.agentcube.volcano.sh\"\n37:     Version   = \"v1alpha1\"\n38: )\n39: ```\n40: \n41: ### Resource Identifiers\n42: \n43: | Resource | Plural | Short Name | Type |\n44: |----------|--------|------------|------|\n45: | AgentRuntime | agentruntimes | ar | AgentRuntime |\n46: | CodeInterpreter | codeinterpreters | ci | CodeInterpreter |\n47: \n48: ### Shared Types\n49: \n50: | Type | Used By | Description |\n51: |------|---------|-------------|\n52: | TargetPort | AgentRuntime, CodeInterpreter | Port configuration with protocol and path |\n53: | ContainerTemplateSpec | CodeInterpreter | Simplified container spec |\n54: | PodTemplateSpec | AgentRuntime | Custom pod template |\n55: | PodSpec | AgentRuntime | Selective pod spec subset |\n56: | ContainerSpec | AgentRuntime | Selective container spec |\n57: | AuthMode | CodeInterpreter | Enum: picod, none |\n58: \n59: ### Helper Functions\n60: \n61: ```go\n62: func Resource(resource string) schema.GroupResource\n63: func AddKnownTypes(scheme *runtime.Scheme) error\n64: ```\n65: \n66: ## Impact Analysis\n67: \n68: ### Dependencies\n69: \n70: | Dependency | Version | Role |\n71: |------------|---------|------|\n72: | `k8s.io/apimachinery/pkg/runtime` | ^1.32 | Scheme, runtime.Object, schema |\n73: | `k8s.io/apimachinery/pkg/apis/meta/v1` | ^1.32 | metav1 types |\n74: \n75: ### Downstream Consumers\n76: \n77: 1. **pkg/apis** ‚Äî Type definitions reference constants\n78: 2. **client-go** ‚Äî Generated clients use Resource() for lister registration\n79: 3. **Controllers** ‚Äî Use constants for scheme registration\n80: 4. **Helm CRDs** ‚Äî CRD generation relies on kubebuilder markers\n81: \n82: ### Risks\n83: \n84: | Risk | Severity | Mitigation |\n85: |------|----------|------------|\n86: | Constant mismatch | High | Single source of truth in register.go |\n87: | Breaking changes | Medium | v1alpha1 is unstable; reserve v1 for stable |\n88: | Type duplication | Low | Shared types in types.go, no duplication |\n89: \n90: ## Alternatives Considered\n91: \n92: ### Alternative 1: Define constants per CRD\n93: \n94: **Approach**: Define GroupName/Version in each CRD type file.\n95: \n96: **Pros**:\n97: - Simple initial implementation\n98: \n99: **Cons**:\n100: - Duplication across files\n101: - Inconsistent values\n102: - Harder to maintain\n103: \n104: **Decision**: Centralized in register.go.\n105: \n106: ### Alternative 2: Use string literals directly\n107: \n108: **Approach**: Hardcode \"runtime.agentcube.volcano.sh\" and \"v1alpha1\" everywhere.\n109: \n110: **Pros**:\n111: - No additional code\n112: \n113: **Cons**:\n114: - No compile-time validation\n115: - Error-prone\n116: - Difficult to refactor\n117: \n118: **Decision**: Use constants for type safety.\n119: \n120: ### Alternative 3: Separate shared package\n121: \n122: **Approach**: Create `pkg/apis/runtime/types/common/` for shared types.\n123: \n124: **Pros**:\n125: - Clear separation\n126: \n127: **Cons**:\n128: - Over-engineering for small project\n129: - More import paths\n130: - Circular dependency risk\n131: \n132: **Decision**: Keep shared types in same package per Kubernetes convention.\n133: \n134: ## Implementation Plan\n135: \n136: 1. Ensure constants in `register.go` match client-go expectations\n137: 2. Verify TargetPort, ContainerTemplateSpec are used by both CRDs\n138: 3. Run `make generate` to produce zz_generated.deepcopy.go\n139: 4. Verify with `make gen-client` ensures client-go compatibility\n140: 5. Verify with `make gen-crd` produces valid CRD YAML\n141: \n142: ## Acceptance Criteria\n143: \n144: - [ ] Constants defined in register.go match API group spec\n145: - [ ] Shared types (TargetPort, ContainerTemplateSpec) are used by both CRDs\n146: - [ ] `make generate` succeeds without errors\n147: - [ ] `make gen-client` succeeds without type errors\n148: - [ ] Go types compile without errors (`go build ./pkg/apis/...`)\n\n(End of file - total 148 lines)\n</content>","metadata":{"preview":"# Proposal: AR-003 ‚Äî CRD ÂÖ±‰∫´Á±ªÂûã‰∏éÂ∏∏Èáè\n\n## Summary\n\nDefine shared types, constants, and utility functions in the `pkg/apis/runtime/v1alpha1` module to support the AgentRuntime and CodeInterpreter CRDs. This includes API group constants, resource identifiers, and common types used across multiple CRDs.\n\n## Purpose\n\nThe shared types and constants provide:\n\n- **API group identification**: Consistent GroupName and Version constants for scheme registration\n- **Resource naming**: Standardized plural resource names for Kubernetes API routing\n- **Client-go compatibility**: Types consumed by generated client library\n- **Type safety**: Shared constants prevent hardcoded strings across the codebase\n\nThese shared definitions are consumed by:\n- pkg/apis (type definitions)\n- client-go library (generated client code)\n- Controllers (workload manager reads CRs)\n- Helm CRDs (generated from types)","truncated":false,"loaded":[]},"title":"workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-MiniMax-M2.5_20260410T163134Z/proposal.md","time":{"start":1775841344165,"end":1775841344187}}}}
