{"type":"step_start","timestamp":1775841345952,"sessionID":"ses_2879c0ebbffeE6Frd5ny1RkJ5L","part":{"id":"prt_d78648197001d4jQZ7NRH03y4v","messageID":"msg_d78647afe001GC4BREGHt2cjmH","sessionID":"ses_2879c0ebbffeE6Frd5ny1RkJ5L","snapshot":"f33c5114db06c230ebdbad281b75532a26b6f114","type":"step-start"}}
{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1775841387376,"sessionID":"ses_2879c0ebbffeE6Frd5ny1RkJ5L","part":{"id":"prt_d78648a8c0016SADrSvU8X7jpD","messageID":"msg_d78647afe001GC4BREGHt2cjmH","sessionID":"ses_2879c0ebbffeE6Frd5ny1RkJ5L","type":"tool","tool":"write","callID":"toolu_d7ff5b1d87084365901f50a4","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"content":"# Proposal: AR-004 ‚Äî WorkloadManager HTTP Service Framework\n\n## Summary\n\nImplement an HTTP service framework in `pkg/workloadmanager` that exposes RESTful APIs for managing AgentRuntime and CodeInterpreter Kubernetes resources. The service integrates with the `github.com/volcano-sh/agentcube/client-go` library to provide CRUD operations and watch functionality.\n\n## Purpose\n\n### Background\nThe WorkloadManager module needs to expose its functionality via HTTP APIs for external clients and internal services to interact with AgentRuntime and CodeInterpreter resources in the Kubernetes cluster.\n\n### Goal\nProvide a production-ready HTTP service framework that:\n- Serves RESTful APIs for AgentRuntime and CodeInterpreter CRUD operations\n- Integrates with the `github.com/volcano-sh/agentcube/client-go` library for Kubernetes API access\n- Follows Kubernetes controller patterns and best practices\n\n### Value\n- Enables external systems to manage AgentRuntime and CodeInterpreter resources programmatically\n- Provides a standardized HTTP interface layer on top of the Kubernetes client\n- Supports observability, middleware extensibility, and graceful shutdown\n\n---\n\n## Scope\n\n### In-Scope\n\n| Deliverable | Description |\n|-------------|-------------|\n| HTTP Server | Configurable host/port with graceful shutdown |\n| Health Endpoints | `/healthz`, `/readyz` for liveness/readiness probes |\n| REST API Endpoints | CRUD operations for AgentRuntime and CodeInterpreter |\n| Client Integration | Integration with client-go Clientset |\n| Middleware | Request logging, metrics, error handling |\n\n### API Endpoints\n\n#### AgentRuntime\n| Method | Path | Description |\n|--------|------|-------------|\n| GET | `/api/v1/namespaces/{namespace}/agentruntimes` | List all AgentRuntimes |\n| POST | `/api/v1/namespaces/{namespace}/agentruntimes` | Create AgentRuntime |\n| GET | `/api/v1/namespaces/{namespace}/agentruntimes/{name}` | Get AgentRuntime |\n| PUT | `/api/v1/namespaces/{namespace}/agentruntimes/{name}` | Update AgentRuntime |\n| DELETE | `/api/v1/namespaces/{namespace}/agentruntimes/{name}` | Delete AgentRuntime |\n| GET | `/api/v1/namespaces/{namespace}/agentruntimes/{name}/status` | Get AgentRuntime status |\n| PATCH | `/api/v1/namespaces/{namespace}/agentruntimes/{name}/status` | Patch AgentRuntime status |\n| GET | `/api/v1/namespaces/{namespace}/agentruntimes?watch=true` | Watch AgentRuntimes |\n\n#### CodeInterpreter\n| Method | Path | Description |\n|--------|------|-------------|\n| GET | `/api/v1/namespaces/{namespace}/codeinterpreters` | List all CodeInterpreters |\n| POST | `/api/v1/namespaces/{namespace}/codeinterpreters` | Create CodeInterpreter |\n| GET | `/api/v1/namespaces/{namespace}/codeinterpreters/{name}` | Get CodeInterpreter |\n| PUT | `/api/v1/namespaces/{namespace}/codeinterpreters/{name}` | Update CodeInterpreter |\n| DELETE | `/api/v1/namespaces/{namespace}/codeinterpreters/{name}` | Delete CodeInterpreter |\n| GET | `/api/v1/namespaces/{namespace}/codeinterpreters/{name}/status` | Get CodeInterpreter status |\n| PATCH | `/api/v1/namespaces/{namespace}/codeinterpreters/{name}/status` | Patch CodeInterpreter status |\n| GET | `/api/v1/namespaces/{namespace}/codeinterpreters?watch=true` | Watch CodeInterpreters |\n\n### Code Structure\n\n```\npkg/workloadmanager/\n‚îú‚îÄ‚îÄ server.go                    # HTTP server implementation\n‚îú‚îÄ‚îÄ router.go                    # Route definitions\n‚îú‚îÄ‚îÄ handler/\n‚îÇ   ‚îú‚îÄ‚îÄ agentruntime.go          # AgentRuntime handlers\n‚îÇ   ‚îú‚îÄ‚îÄ codeinterpreter.go       # CodeInterpreter handlers\n‚îÇ   ‚îî‚îÄ‚îÄ handler.go               # Shared handler utilities\n‚îú‚îÄ‚îÄ middleware/\n‚îÇ   ‚îú‚îÄ‚îÄ logging.go               # Request logging\n‚îÇ   ‚îú‚îÄ‚îÄ metrics.go               # Metrics collection\n‚îÇ   ‚îî‚îÄ‚îÄ error.go                 # Error handling\n‚îú‚îÄ‚îÄ client/\n‚îÇ   ‚îî‚îÄ‚îÄ client.go                # Kubernetes client wrapper\n‚îî‚îÄ‚îÄ config/\n    ‚îî‚îÄ‚îÄ config.go                # Server configuration\n```\n\n### Out-of-Scope\n- Custom Resource Definitions (CRDs) ‚Äî already defined in `pkg/apis/runtime/v1alpha1`\n- Controller/reconciler logic ‚Äî separate concern\n- WebSocket or streaming APIs (beyond Kubernetes watch)\n- Authentication/Authorization (pluggable hooks only)\n- Rate limiting (future enhancement)\n\n---\n\n## Impact Analysis\n\n### Dependencies\n\n| Dependency | Source | Purpose |\n|------------|--------|---------|\n| github.com/volcano-sh/agentcube/client-go | local | Kubernetes typed client |\n| k8s.io/client-go/rest | ^0.34 | Low-level REST client |\n| k8s.io/apimachinery/pkg/runtime | ^1.34 | Object serialization |\n| k8s.io/apimachinery/pkg/api/errors | ^1.34 | Kubernetes API errors |\n| k8s.io/apimachinery/pkg/apis/meta/v1 | ^1.34 | metav1 types |\n\n### Downstream Consumers\n\n1. **External CLI tools** ‚Äî Manage AgentRuntime/CodeInterpreter resources\n2. **Webhook services** ‚Äî Integrate with admission controllers\n3. **Monitoring systems** ‚Äî Query resource status via HTTP\n4. **CI/CD pipelines** ‚Äî Deploy workloads programmatically\n\n### Risks\n\n| Risk | Severity | Mitigation |\n|------|----------|------------|\n| Client resource leaks | High | Proper client lifecycle management |\n| API compatibility | Medium | Version prefixes for API stability |\n| Error propagation | Medium | Proper HTTP status code mapping |\n\n---\n\n## Alternatives Considered\n\n### Option 1: Standard Go net/http (Selected)\n\n**Approach**: Use Go's built-in `net/http` package for HTTP server implementation.\n\n**Pros**:\n- Full control over server behavior\n- No additional dependencies\n- Lightweight and minimal\n- Follows Kubernetes apiserver patterns\n\n**Cons**:\n- Must implement routing from scratch\n- Middleware must be built manually\n\n**Decision**: Selected for maximum flexibility and minimal dependencies.\n\n---\n\n### Option 2: Gin/Echo Framework\n\n**Approach**: Use third-party HTTP framework like Gin or Echo.\n\n**Pros**:\n- Rich routing capabilities\n- Built-in middleware ecosystem\n- Request validation helpers\n\n**Cons**:\n- Additional external dependency\n- Potential version drift\n- Overhead for simple use case\n\n**Decision**: Rejected ‚Äî adds unnecessary complexity for Kubernetes controller context.\n\n---\n\n### Option 3: Kubernetes API Server Aggregation\n\n**Approach**: Implement as Kubernetes API server aggregation layer.\n\n**Pros**:\n- Native Kubernetes integration\n- Built-in authentication/authorization\n- Standard Kubernetes client compatibility\n\n**Cons**:\n- Complex setup and configuration\n- Requires API server configuration\n- Higher resource footprint\n\n**Decision**: Rejected ‚Äî separate feature, not within current scope.\n\n---\n\n### Option 4: gRPC with grpc-gateway\n\n**Approach**: Use gRPC for internal communication with grpc-gateway for REST.\n\n**Pros**:\n- Type-safe service definitions\n- Streaming support\n- High performance\n\n**Cons**:\n- Requires protobuf definitions\n- Additional complexity\n- gRPC not required for current use case\n\n**Decision**: Rejected ‚Äî gRPC not required for current HTTP API requirements.\n\n---\n\n## Implementation Plan\n\n### Phase 1: Core Server\n- [ ] Implement `server.go` with configurable host/port\n- [ ] Add graceful shutdown handling\n- [ ] Create health check endpoints (`/healthz`, `/readyz`)\n\n### Phase 2: Client Integration\n- [ ] Create Kubernetes client wrapper in `client/client.go`\n- [ ] Integrate with client-go `Clientset`\n- [ ] Handle config loading (in-cluster, kubeconfig)\n\n### Phase 3: Router & Handlers\n- [ ] Implement `router.go` with route definitions\n- [ ] Create AgentRuntime handlers\n- [ ] Create CodeInterpreter handlers\n- [ ] Add list/watch support\n\n### Phase 4: Middleware\n- [ ] Add request logging middleware\n- [ ] Add metrics collection\n- [ ] Implement error handling middleware\n\n### Phase 5: Testing\n- [ ] Unit tests for handlers\n- [ ] Integration tests with fake clientset\n- [ ] End-to-end tests against mock API server\n\n---\n\n## Acceptance Criteria\n\n- [ ] HTTP server starts and listens on configured port\n- [ ] Health endpoints (`/healthz`, `/readyz`) return 200 OK\n- [ ] All CRUD operations for AgentRuntime work correctly\n- [ ] All CRUD operations for CodeInterpreter work correctly\n- [ ] Watch endpoints stream properly\n- [ ] Kubernetes client is properly managed (no resource leaks)\n- [ ] Request logging captures relevant details\n- [ ] Errors are properly mapped to HTTP status codes\n- [ ] Unit tests pass with >80% coverage for handlers\n- [ ] Server handles graceful shutdown within 30 seconds","filePath":"/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-MiniMax-M2.5_20260410T163134Z/proposal.md"},"output":"Wrote file successfully.","metadata":{"diagnostics":{},"filepath":"/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-MiniMax-M2.5_20260410T163134Z/proposal.md","exists":true,"truncated":false},"title":"workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-MiniMax-M2.5_20260410T163134Z/proposal.md","time":{"start":1775841387341,"end":1775841387374}}}}
